lines.text:
WHEN HE HELD ME IN HIS ARMS,
                I NEVER

WANTED TO LEAVE HIM... NEVER
                WANTED TO

GO BACK TO THAT HOUSE. BUT I
                HAD TO..

THERE WERE RULES TO BE
                FOLLOWED. THE

HIS LIPS CAME SLOWLY CLOSER.
                I WANTED HIM

TO KISS ME, BUT I ENJOYED THE
                TINGLING

THRILL OF WAITING... I KNEW
                IT WASN'T JUST
I CAN'T KID MYSELF ANY MORE,

SUDDENLY, WITHOUT A WORD OF
                WARNING, THE MOOD WAS BROKEN BY A HARSH,

STILL WARM FROM BILL'S
                EMBRACE, I WAS CONFUSED AND UNABLE TO

THINK. I WANTED TO CALM THEM
                DOWN BEFORE SOMETHING TERRIBLE

I SHOULD HAVE SPOKEN UP
                AGAINST GLORIA AT ONCE, BUT I

WAS SO AFRAID BILL WOULD
                LEAVE.. AND I WANTED TO CALM

HER DOWN. I DIDN'T EXPECT
                BILL'S REACTION!
